The paper deals with the verification of population protocols, which are a model of distributed computation. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). However, the paper specifically focuses on the well-specification problem for population protocols, which is a question of formal verification. This falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the well-specification problem, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper introduces a new class of protocols, WS3, which is suitable for automatic verification. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY), as it involves developing algorithms for automated reasoning. Overall, the most likely categories are cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.SC, cs.SY, and cs.AI.
